									<div class="comment-content" itemprop="text">
										<p>Hi Amic,</p>
										<p>I didn&#8217;t write this post to teach people how to use LSI, but that it was likely that Google doesn&#8217;t use LSI and that it does use other approaches. I linked to the Patent that came out in the late 1980s and early 1990s, and a couple of papers about LSI. I am suggesting that you don&#8217;t try to use LSI for SEO because it is possible that it isn&#8217;t going to help you much. There are other ways to use semantic approaches to improve your pages, and the content on them. For instance, I gave a presentation in Pubcon a couple of months ago, where I talked about some of those. The presentation can be found here:</p>
										<p>Semantic Keyword Research and Topic Models<br />
											<a href="http://www.seobythesea.com/2017/11/semantic-keyword-research-topic-models/" rel="nofollow">http://www.seobythesea.com/2017/11/semantic-keyword-research-topic-models/</a></p>
